    "text": "Tim, you might want to have a look at what Richard Pawson did for the Irish government. See for example <https://www.infoq.com/presentations/Large-scale-Pure-OO-Irish-Government/?itm_source=presentations_about_Naked_Objects&amp;itm_medium=link&amp;itm_campaign=Naked_Objects|https://www.infoq.com/presentations/Large-scale-Pure-OO-Irish-Government/?itm_sourc[…]about_Naked_Objects&amp;itm_medium=link&amp;itm_campaign=Naked_Objects>. It is a completely different way of looking at the automation (you're not automating the process, your automating the tools to allow people to do their work). I'm really a big fan of Richard's work. Don't let the awkward naming or weird user interface fool you. The power is having tools that help people instead of hinder them (because of fixed processes, rigid rules, etc).",
    "user": "URKQXRCAC",
    "ts": "1609533610.183700",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
